so how does it know what rules to follow while doing the extraction?

Great question!

Let me give you a clear and honest answer:

In the script I gave you earlier:
The current script does NOT know any smart rules.

It follows very basic, fixed rules only:

Extract all text from every page (in reading order)
Split it by pages
Save everything as raw text inside JSON
If you enable tables → it tries to detect rectangular tables and saves them as lists of lists
That’s it.

It does not understand:

What is an “invoice number”
What is a “total amount”
What is a “customer name”
How to separate sections like “Header”, “Items”, “Footer”
How to handle different layouts
It is a dumb extractor — fast and reliable for getting the text out, but not intelligent.

So how can we make it follow proper “rules”?
There are 3 levels of intelligence you can add:

Level	How Smart?	How it Works	Best For
1	Basic (current script)	Fixed rules + raw text	Quick dump of text
2	Rule-based / Template	You define patterns (regex, keywords, positions)	Invoices, bank statements, fixed forms
3	AI-powered (LLM)	Use GPT / Grok / Claude / Llama to understand the document	Any complex or varied PDFs
Since you have a lot of PDFs, I recommend we go with Level 2 or Level 3 depending on your needs.

