Explain Level 3 LLM extraction

Level 3 LLM Extraction is the most intelligent and flexible way to convert PDFs → JSON.

It is the exact method I used to create the JSON I just gave you for the May 2024 SP1 papers.

Simple Comparison of the 3 Levels
Level	Name	How it works	Intelligence	Accuracy for complex PDFs	Speed	Best for
1	Basic / Raw	Fixed rules (PyMuPDF + pdfplumber)	None	Low	Very fast	Simple text dump
2	Rule-based / Template	Regex + keywords + position rules	Low	Medium	Fast	Fixed-format docs (invoices, forms)
3	AI-powered (LLM)	Large Language Model understands the whole document	High	Very High	Fast (once schema is set)	Exam papers, reports, solutions, mixed layouts
What Level 3 Actually Does (Step-by-Step)
Full Document Understanding
The LLM reads every page, every image, every layout element (headings, sub-headings, numbered lists, mark allocations, page footers, etc.).
Semantic + Contextual Reasoning
It doesn’t just extract text — it understands:
“This is Question 1(i)” → belongs to Q1 part i
“(2)” at the end of a line → marks for that part
“Solution 1:” in the solution PDF → belongs to Question 1
Which text is header/footer/page number (and removes it automatically)
Which text is examiner instruction vs actual answer
Exact Mapping to Your Desired Schema
You give one clear JSON template (like the April 2025 example you attached).
The LLM then forces every extracted piece into that exact structure:
label, questions, scenario, parts, marks, question, Indicative Solution array, themes, etc.
Automatically calculates total marks = 100
Handles “Refer question” when a question starts directly with sub-parts
Keeps verbatim text (no paraphrasing) for both QP and Solution
Cross-PDF Pairing
In your case I received two separate PDFs:
SP1 IAI 2024 May2024 QP.pdf (questions)
SP1 IAI 2024 May2024 Solution.pdf (indicative solutions)
Level 3 automatically matches every solution to its question even when they are in different documents.
Cleaning
It automatically removes:
“IAI SP1-0524”, “Page X of 14”, “INDICATIVE SOLUTION”, examiner intro text, footers, etc.
Only the clean question/solution text remains.
Why Level 3 is Perfect for Your Use Case
Your PDFs have varying layouts across different sittings → rules (Level 2) would break.
You need exact verbatim text for both questions and solutions.
You want consistent JSON structure across 10+ years of past papers.
You want automatic mark allocation and total = 100.
You have hundreds of PDFs → once the schema is fixed, Level 3 can process them all in batch with almost zero manual correction.
How I Applied Level 3 to Your May 2024 PDFs
